# TASK 9 – Exception Handling & Logging in Python

## Objective
To understand and implement exception handling and logging in Python for building production-ready applications.

## Tools Used
- Python
- logging module

##  Files
- error_handling.py → main script
- app.log → log file storing error details

## Concepts Covered
- try-except blocks
- Multiple exception handling
- else and finally usage
- Custom exceptions
- Logging errors to a file
- Debugging using logs

##  How It Works
- Handles runtime errors like ZeroDivisionError and TypeError
- Uses a custom exception for negative numbers
- Logs all errors with timestamps into `app.log`

## Sample Errors Simulated
- Division by zero
- Invalid data type
- Negative input values

## Outcome
This task helps build robust, maintainable, and production-ready Python code.
